# Tech & UX Bias: Newer at Same Cost

The reference site `cipassoroma/` (CiPASSO, cipassoitalia.it) is a **structural and stylistic guide only** — not a technology blueprint. When choosing tools, libraries, or UI patterns for Haivino:

## The rule

> **Prefer the newer / better option** when its **cost is the same or lower** than the equivalent on the reference site.

"Cost" includes all of:
- License / hosting price
- Developer effort to set up and maintain
- Learning curve for the user (if they will edit content)
- Performance / accessibility / SEO budget

If a modern alternative wins on capability and is **not** more expensive on any of those axes, choose it.

## Concrete defaults (revise as the stack matures)

| Area | Reference (CiPASSO) | Default for Haivino |
|------|---------------------|---------------------|
| Site type | WordPress + page builder | Static-site / SSG (Astro, Next.js static, SvelteKit) — unless the user needs a CMS |
| Styling | Theme CSS + builder | Tailwind CSS or modern CSS (logical properties, container queries, `:has`) |
| Images | Theme-served | `<picture>` + AVIF/WebP, responsive `srcset`, lazy-load, `loading="lazy"` |
| Fonts | Theme defaults | Self-hosted variable fonts, `font-display: swap`, preloaded |
| Animations | Marquee, fade-ins via builder JS | CSS-only where possible; `prefers-reduced-motion` respected; View Transitions API if useful |
| Forms | CF7 / WPForms | Native HTML5 + serverless function (Cloudflare Workers / Netlify / Vercel) or Formspree-style |
| Booking | External embedded widget | Same pattern is fine, but the trigger must be accessible and lazy-loaded |
| i18n | WPML / Polylang | Framework-native i18n routing (e.g. Astro i18n, Next.js routing) |
| Accessibility | Not verified | WCAG 2.2 AA target; keyboard-navigable; focus-visible; semantic HTML |
| SEO | Yoast | Built-in metadata + JSON-LD `Restaurant` schema; clean working sitemap |
| Analytics | Unknown | Privacy-friendly (Plausible / Umami / Cloudflare Web Analytics) over GA |
| Cookie banner | Iubenda-style | Only if actually needed; minimize tracking so consent isn't required |

## What to copy from CiPASSO

Page rhythm, content sectioning, value-prop quartets, marquee bands, sticky bilingual booking CTA, the editorial tone. See `cipassoroma/06-design-and-ux-notes.md` and `cipassoroma/07-adaptation-ideas-for-haivino.md`.

## What to deliberately improve

- A **real menu** on the menu page (HTML, structured, with allergens) — not just a PDF embed.
- A **working sitemap** and accessible booking trigger.
- **Native-quality copy** in each language — never literal machine translation.
- **No duplicated DOM blocks** (the reference site renders sections twice).

## When in doubt

If a modern choice would cost the user more (paid SaaS, complex CMS, heavier hosting), flag the trade-off and let the user decide via a multiple-choice question rather than picking silently.
